<HEADLINE>
<P>
FEINSTEIN, WILSON CAMPAIGNS FOR GOVERNORSHIP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wilson's rhetoric is very familiar. Like George Bush, when running for 
President, Wilson pledges to be the "education governor." 
</P>
<P>
However, he is part of the same class of politicians who have seen constant 
cuts in education -- Ronald Reagan, George Deukmejian and Bush. We cannot 
afford another clone of Reaganomics for our state. 
</P>
<P>
GWEN KOZMAN 
</P>
<P>
Irvine 
</P>
