<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: STAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Play Delay: "M. Butterfly" won't arrive at the Wilshire Theatre in Beverly 
Hills until March or July, said a spokesman for the touring production of the 
Tony-winning play, which just opened in Boston with a $1-million advance sale. 
The Los Angeles run had been scheduled for Dec. 4-30, but the spokesman said 
the producers now want a longer Los Angeles stay -- of at least five weeks -- 
and the only openings in the show's tour that would allow the longer run are in 
March or July. BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
