<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Winn-Dixie Stores Inc.: The Jacksonville, Fla.-based retailer said 
first-quarter net income dipped 2% to $24.3 million, while revenue rose 5.3% to 
$2.284 billion. The firm said the results were affected by a new 
everyday-low-price program in its largest division. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Corporate Earnings 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA100490-0030 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 286952 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
October 4, 1990, Thursday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Business; Part D; Page 2; Column 1; Financial Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
52 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Safeway Inc.: The food retailer reported third-quarter net profit of $20.8 
million, nearly three times the $7.1 million reported for the same quarter of 
last year. Revenue for the period was $3.5 billion, up 4.6% from last year. The 
Oakland-based company attributed the strong showing to better management. 
</P>
</TEXT>
