<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: WESTCHESTER; 
</P>
<P>
LOYOLA CAR-POOLING PLAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
More than 100 of nearly 800 faculty and staff members at Loyola Marymount 
University are leaving their cars at home and car pooling to work to save 
energy and reduce pollution. 
</P>
<P>
Ray Hilyar, the school's director of public safety, said car pooling was 
organized at the school in response to Air Quality Management District 
regulations aimed at reducing car travel. 
</P>
<P>
Employees who participate in the program are given choice campus parking spots 
and free parking permits. In addition, participants are provided free 
transportation in cases of emergency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
