<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: BALDWIN HILLS; 
</P>
<P>
PUBLIC SERVICE WORKSHOP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles City Councilwoman Ruth Galanter will host a workshop designed to 
help residents of Baldwin Hills, Crenshaw, and Leimert Park improve their 
communities by learning how to deal with government and private agencies. 
</P>
<P>
The workshop will run from 9 a.m. to 3:30 p.m. on Oct. 13, at the Good Shepherd 
Episcopal Church, 3033 W. Vernon Ave. It will cover crime prevention, land-use 
planning, human relations, and other areas. 
</P>
<P>
Organizers said seating for the workshop is limited. For information, call 
Valerie Shaw at (213) 485-3305. 
</P>
</TEXT>
