<HEADLINE>
<P>
BEST BETS: MARITIME CELEBRATIONS PLANNED AT TWO PORTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A festive mood will pervade Port Hueneme and Oxnard this weekend as the two 
communities hold annual celebrations. 
</P>
<P>
The 36th Annual Port Hueneme Harbor Days will be held 9:30 a.m. to 4 p.m. 
Saturday and Sunday at Hueneme Beach, Ventura Road and Surfside Drive. 
</P>
<P>
The weekend includes a parade on Saturday at 10:30 a.m., arts and crafts 
exhibits, carnival games booths, pony rides for the kids, entertainment and 
plenty of food and drink. 
</P>
<P>
Featured events will be a sand sculpture contest and a kite-flying 
demonstration. 
</P>
<P>
For information call 487-4470 or 483-8146. 
</P>
<P>
Oxnard's fourth annual Maritime Days also takes place on Saturday and Sunday, 
10 a.m. to 5 p.m., and will be held at Channel Islands Harbor, marking the 25th 
anniversary of the port. 
</P>
<P>
Participants can view classic yachts and enjoy schooner races, arts and crafts 
booths, a chowder cook-off and more. A full schedule of entertainment, 
including children's events, is available. 
</P>
<P>
For more information, call 485-5255. 
</P>
