'SOUTH WON'T RISE AGAIN,' CONFEDERATE FLAG THIEF DECLARES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MONTGOMERY, Ala. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Confederate battle flag was stolen from its perch atop Alabama's historic 
Capitol in a pre-dawn theft Wednesday apparently by a man who told a news 
organization: "The South won't rise again." 
</P>
<P>
A new Rebel standard was back in place by 9 a.m. flying below the Stars and 
Stripes and the Alabama state flag, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The Confederate flag, a target of protest by critics who contend that it 
symbolizes slave-era racial oppression, was hauled down by an intruder in the 
Capitol, the site where Jefferson Davis was inaugurated as president of the 
Confederacy in 1861. 
</P>
<P>
The Capitol is closed and mostly empty for restoration work. 
</P>
