</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Moreno Valley, a rapidly growing city in Riverside County, opened its first 
hospital, a 96-bed facility to be managed as a joint venture of the Hemet 
Valley Hospital District and St. Joseph Health System of Orange. 
</P>
<P>
Previously, residents had to travel to Riverside or Loma Linda for hospital 
care. The Moreno Valley Medical Center occupies a 20-acre site at 27300 Iris 
Ave., cost $42 million to build and is designed to accommodate expansion up to 
250 beds, according to spokesman Larry Berenato. Hemet Valley Hospital 
District, which owns two other nonprofit hospitals in Riverside County, 
financed the project through revenue bonds which it expects to retire with 
hospital income. 
