<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY DIGEST: SOUTH GATE; 
</P>
<P>
PUBLIC WORKS DIRECTOR HIRED TO REPLACE RETIREE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council has hired James A. Biery as public works director to replace 
Rollie Berry, who retired in July. 
</P>
<P>
Biery, 40, was given a three-year contract at an estimated $76,000 a year. For 
the past nine years, he has been director of public works and city engineer for 
Signal Hill. He has more than 17 years of experience in the field of public 
works, including work as a civil engineer for Los Angeles County and the cities 
of Seal Beach and Montclair in San Bernardino County. 
</P>
<P>
Biery has a bachelor's degree in civil engineering from USC and master's 
degrees in civil engineering and public administration from Cal State Long 
Beach. 
</P>
</TEXT>
