<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY DIGEST: DOWNEY; 
</P>
<P>
SCHOOL BOARD VACANCY TO BE FILLED BY APPOINTMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A vacant seat on the nine-member Board of Education of the Downey Unified 
School District will be filled by appointment, a district official announced 
this week. 
</P>
<P>
The Area 5 seat was vacated by veteran board member Walter S. Temple, who 
resigned Sept. 30 because he moved out of the school district. 
</P>
<P>
Applications for the post will be accepted until Oct. 24. To be eligible, 
candidates must be at least 18 years old, registered to vote in Los Angeles 
County, and residents of the district's Area 5. Most of Area 5 is south of 
Firestone Boulevard, between Rives Avenue and Lakewood Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
The board is expected to fill the vacancy before the end of November. The 
appointment will be for one year, until the district's next regular election in 
November, 1991. 
</P>
</TEXT>
