<P>
TEAM IS WAITING PATIENTLY FOR BO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS DUFRESNE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bo Jackson, football's Mr. October, has finished his summer of baseball with 
the Kansas City Royals and is expected to join the Raiders soon. How soon? 
</P>
<P>
"Bo will let us know when he's going to arrive," Raider Coach Art Shell said 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Jackson usually takes a week or so to refuel his jets. Shell isn't saying how 
Jackson will be used in a backfield already stocked with Marcus Allen and Greg 
Bell. 
</P>
<P>
"When he gets here, he'll practice, he'll work and he'll get into the rotation 
like everyone else," Shell said. 
</P>
<P>
Does Bo do anything like anyone else? 
</P>
<P>
Shell said defensive end Mike Wise's ankle is better, but no decision has been 
made on whether he'll play Sunday night against the Bills in Buffalo. CHRIS 
DUFRESNE 
</P>
