<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: LATE GOAL FROM ADAIR LIFTS USD PAST CAL, 2-1 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Charles Adair, a sophomore transfer from San Diego State, scored with 4 minutes 
8 seconds remaining to lift the University of San Diego men's soccer team to a 
2-1 nonconference victory over Cal Wednesday at USD. 
</P>
<P>
USD (7-1-4) returned to its winning ways after losing for the first time 
Friday, 2-0, to San Francisco, which snapped the Toreros' 13-match unbeaten 
streak dating back to last season. 
</P>
<P>
USD's Paul Gelvezon opened the scoring at 1:49 with his eighth goal on assists 
from Leo Ronces and goalie Tom Tate, who made a long outlet pass. 
</P>
<P>
At 66:48, Cal's Tom Barker scored with Paul Woodring getting the assist. 
Adair's winner, his first goal, came off an assist by Ronces. 
</P>
<P>
Andy Morrene scored two first-half goals to lead San Diego State past Biola, 
4-0, in a nonconference match at SDSU. Shane Hickson and Pat Merrell scored the 
other goals for SDSU (7-4-1). Curtis McAlister and Chris Volk combined to shut 
out Biola (6-5-1). 
</P>
<P>
Point Loma Nazarene scored a come-from-behind, 3-2 Golden State Athletic 
Conference victory over Cal Baptist in Riverside. Trailing, 2-1, Todd Bernard 
scored with an assist from Mark Vogel with 10 minutes left, and Robert Romero 
scored off a pass from Steve Cokkinis with 5:00 to go. Cokkinis scored the 
Crusaders' first goal. Cal Baptist fell to 2-9-1, 0-2. Saturday, PLNC (4-3-1, 
2-0) plays host to Westmont, ranked fourth in the NAIA. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
WOMEN'S SOCCER 
</P>
<P>
Dawn Evans scored in the 65th minute to give UC Irvine a 1-0 nonconference 
victory over USIU. UC Irvine (5-5-1) set school records with its fifth 
consecutive victory and its fifth consecutive shutout. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
WOMEN'S VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
Setter Shannon Mutch had 47 assists and 19 digs to lead USD over U.S. 
International, 15-9, 15-12, 15-9, at the M. Larry Lawrence Jewish Community 
Center. Andrea Bruns had 16 kills for USD (7-10). USIU (5-13) was led by 
Heather Kelley with 18 kills. 
</P>
<P>
UC San Diego, the top-ranked NCAA Division III team, had little trouble 
defeating Biola, 15-7, 15-3, 15-4, in a nonconference match in La Jolla. Vikki 
Van Duyne had 10 kills and Elizabeth Tan seven for UCSD, which improved to 
20-4. 
</P>
<P>
Freshman setter Julie Fabian, making her first college start in place of 
injured starter Amy Banachowski, had 32 assists. Biola fell to 8-10. 
</P>
</TEXT>
