</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council on Tuesday approved the development of a $300,000 sports 
complex to be used by the Monrovia Youth Baseball League at Santa Fe 
Intermediate School. 
</P>
<P>
Construction will begin this month on the complex, which includes baseball 
fields, bleachers, two scoreboards and portable fencing. 
</P>
<P>
