<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: ALHAMBRA; 
</P>
<P>
AUTO THEFT PROGRAM TO BEGIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Starting Saturday, Alhambra residents can take advantage of a free program to 
crack down on auto theft. 
</P>
<P>
The "Combat Auto Theft" program is already in operation in other cities, 
including Monrovia, Ventura, Van Nuys and Anaheim. Participating drivers place 
a special decal in their car's right rear window and sign a document promising 
not to drive between the hours of 1 a.m. and 5 a.m. A patrol officer who spots 
a car with a decal on the road between those hours will be alerted to a 
possible stolen vehicle. 
</P>
<P>
City officials will begin registering residents for the program Saturday from 
10 a.m. to 2 p.m. at the parking lot on the north side of City Hall, 111 S. 1st 
St. 
</P>
