SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: AZUSA; 
</P>
<P>
TOW-AWAY RATES INCREASED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Parking in a tow-away zone just got more expensive. 
</P>
<P>
The City Council on Monday unanimously raised the rates. 
</P>
<P>
Owners of impounded cars will pay $59 for towing, up from $53.50. Storage 
charges have been raised to $10 a day, up from $9. 
</P>
<P>
Byron Nelson, interim police chief, recommended raising the tow-away rates to 
bring them into line with those in other areas of Los Angeles County. 
</P>
