<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: LA VERNE; 
</P>
<P>
NEW CITY ATTORNEY CHOSEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After considering candidates from 16 law firms, the City Council on Monday 
named Robert Kress the new city attorney. 
</P>
<P>
Kress, of the Santa Monica firm Wallin, Kress, Reisman, Price &amp; Dilkes, 
took over from Scott Smith of the Riverside firm Best, Best &amp; Krieger. 
Best, Best &amp; Krieger is being retained as special legal counsel to handle 
continuing legal business. 
</P>
<P>
Councilman Thomas R. Harvey, who earlier this year suggested a change in city 
attorneys, said he felt Best, Best &amp; Krieger could have better defended a 
lawsuit seeking to block a proposed Edwards theater complex. 
</P>
</TEXT>
