<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE NEWS: POMONA PROFESSOR GETS RESEARCH AWARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pomona College chemistry professor Wayne Steinmetz has received a Partners in 
Science Award from Research Corp. to continue work on erythromycin begun last 
summer. 
</P>
<P>
The program links high school science teachers with college researchers to 
improve secondary science education. 
</P>
<P>
Steinmetz is working on the project with Richard Bersch, a science teacher at 
Glendora High School. 
</P>
</TEXT>
