<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSBITES: DINNER GUESTS WILL HAVE A VINE TIME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BEVERLY BUSH SMITH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two California central coast wineries -- Maison Deutz and Meridian Vineyards -- 
will share the spotlight at a winemaker dinner Tuesday, Oct. 9, at John Dominis 
in Newport Beach. Food and wine match-ups include rare seared Hawaiian red tuna 
and a lobster spinach flan, served with 1988 Edna Valley Chardonnay. 
</P>
<P>
Tim Hanni, of Meridian Winery, one of only two Americans to successfully 
complete the Master of Wine exam in London, will discuss the wines. Reception 
begins at 7 p.m., dinner at 7:30. Cost: $50 per person, including tax and 
gratuity. John Dominis is at 2901 W. Coast Highway, Newport Beach. 
Reservations: (714) 650-5112. 
</P>
<P>
The Robert Mondavi Wine &amp; Food Center will present a Baroque Dinner Concert 
at 7 p.m. Friday, Oct. 5. Dinner delicacies include Italian fall white truffle 
manicotti with ricotta cheese and tarragon cream sauce, and red currant 
marinated loin of lamb with sweet corn souffle and rosemary polenta. The 
chamber performance, conducted by Keith Clark, includes music of Bach, Vivaldi, 
Handel. Dinner and concert: $100. Reservations: (714) 979-4510. The food center 
is at 1570 Scenic Ave., Costa Mesa. BEVERLY BUSH SMITH 
</P>
