<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEEDED PLAYERS TAKE COURT TODAY IN TENNIS EVENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pepperdine, UCLA and USC combined to send seven players to the second round of 
play in the inaugural West Coast Fall Men's Championships, a tennis tournament 
at Warner Center Club in Woodland Hills. 
</P>
<P>
Twelve seeded players, led by No. 1-ranked Bill Behrens of UCLA, were granted 
first-round byes and open play today. 
</P>
<P>
Behrens plays Paul Tracy of UC Irvine, who defeated Jason Colter of Azusa 
Pacific by default. 
</P>
<P>
Third-seeded David Ekcrote of USC also begins play today, meeting Cal State 
Bakersfield's Kurt Kopp, who won by default over Alex Ray of Pepperdine. In 
another match, fourth-seeded Andros Lanyi of USC will play UC Irvine's Rodger 
Vig, a 6-1, 6-4 winner over Oscar Tarre-Miro of Bakersfield. Play begins at 10 
a.m. The final will be played Sunday at noon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
