<HEADLINE>
<P>
FULLERTON BAND WINS CONTEST, TOKYO DATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE BOEHM 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Stikkitty, a hard-rock band from Fullerton, will receive $10,000 and a date at 
Tokyo's famous Budokhan Theatre as winner of a national contest for unsigned 
rock bands. 
</P>
<P>
The "Soundcheck" contest finals took place Tuesday night at the Roxy in 
Hollywood and were judged by a panel of record producers and major label talent 
scouts. 
</P>
<P>
Stikkitty defeated four other contenders -- from Santa Monica, Detroit, Atlanta 
and New York City -- after each band played two original songs. 
</P>
<P>
Stikkitty's singer, Vincent K., also received $1,000 as outstanding vocalist in 
the contest, which is sponsored by Yamaha. Another Stikkitty member, Dwayne 
Allen, won $1,000 as outstanding bassist. Stikkitty, which also includes 
guitarist John Gurzi and drummer David Outzs, will represent the United States 
at "Band Explosion," an international rock festival in Tokyo on Oct. 28. MIKE 
BOEHM 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
STIKKITTY (MUSIC GROUP); CONTESTS; BANDS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA100490-0206 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 287452 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
October 4, 1990, Thursday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
