<HEADLINE>
<P>
HAVING THEIR CAKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The article and recipe for the "secret-ingredient cake" was interesting. But 
it's still a very high-fat and high-calorie dessert. I believe it might be 
possible to make a very good-tasting, low-calorie, low-fat cake with these 
revisions: 
</P>
<P>
Instead of 3 eggs, use 6 egg whites. 
</P>
<P>
Cut the sugar amount from 1 3/4 cups to 1 1/2 cups. Instead of using 1 1/4 cups 
of oil, use 1 1/4 cups of applesauce. Delete the 1 1/4 teaspoons of salt from 
the recipe. 
</P>
<P>
I've analyzed both recipe versions with Nutritionist III software. You'll note 
that the calories are reduced by 53% (283 to 133 calories), and cholesterol is 
eliminated completely. Only a tenth of a serving/exchange of vegetables (3 
calories) results from the addition of the beans -- I'd be tempted to sneak in 
double that amount at least. 
</P>
<P>
 -- JIM GRIZZELL, M.A., health educator, California State Polytechnic 
University, Pomona 
</P>
</TEXT>
